Node.Label: OC
Node.Notes: Connected to Hebrew word for camp; apparently two camps (though reason for naming this place two camps is not clear; see commentaries for some guesses).
Assumes: he will strike me [and he will strike] mother with children.
Jacob is the main target, and apparently proverbial phrase mother upon/to children is added to suggest a cruel, merciless slaughter.
Repetition of herd in distributive sense, plus by itself: each herd by itself.
A shallow place in a river or stream where people and animals can cross to the other side.
Flows westward to join the Jordan about 25 miles north of the Dead Sea. Known today as Wadi Zerga.

Node.Notes: This name apparently means the face of EL (a common word for God).
